[thinking] **Exploring Java inner classes**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about inner classes in interfaces. They are implicitly public static, right? I wonder if they can be protected. When I look at the bytecode, it seems a protected abstract class is possible. But Java source itself doesn't allow a protected class inside an interface, which is interesting. It's like I should try to mimic that class structure to see how it behaves. There’s quite a bit to unpack here!
