[thinking] **Evaluating Security Manager in Java**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm trying to figure out if `System.setSecurityManager` compiles in the current JDK, likely JDK 21. It seems that while it might compile with deprecation, it won't work at runtime in Java 25 due to JEP 486 disabling it permanently in JDK 24; calling it throws an `UnsupportedOperationException`. Also, `getSecurityManager` returns null. I wonder if it's possible to alter the static SYSTEM field to return a non-null value safely, but that also seems tricky with reflection or Unsafe.
[thinking] 
