[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m looking into whether the dynamic report can accept a helper method. It seems that I should avoid direct reflection in tests unless it's a natural public API requirement. I might consider defining a test class in the same package using Byte Buddy's JavaDispatcher. To access non-null static fields, I could use `ClassInjector.UsingReflection.DISPATCHER` to call private static fields. Also, I wonder if I can install a SecurityManager for compatible JDK versions by adding `-Djava.security.manager=allow` in Gradle's jvmArgs.
[thinking] 
