[assistant] Fixed the `SYSTEM` restoration issue.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - The helper temporarily replaced Byte Buddy’s `ClassInjector.UsingReflection.SYSTEM` to exercise the security-manager branch in `UsingUnsafeOverride.initialize()`.
[assistant] - On this JDK, the original `SYSTEM` value can be `null`, so restoring that `null` caused subsequent dispatcher initialization to throw `NullPointerException`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change:
[assistant] - `UnsafeOverrideDispatcherAccess.exerciseSecurityManagerPermissionCheck()` now restores the original `SYSTEM` when non-null.
